# (US) English labeleing reference dictionary.
# Usable for non-US english too with some consideration.
# Words taken from CMU dict, phonemes scraped from the internet, and manually segmented and corrected.

# note: fix inconsistency with [l / y] in ~100 words. some words should be <l y> in single syllable.
# note: fix inconsistency with [* / r] in ~100 words. some words should be <* r> in single syllable.
# note: fix inconsistency with [uh] used in some placed where [ah] should be used. Especially for compound words.
# note: [d] is missing in some words ending in "-nds". Up for debate as some may drop the [d] entirely. Label [d] if pause between [n] and [s].

# note: words like "carry" are transcribed as [k eh - r iy] instead of [k ae r - iy]
	as moving the rhotic to the syllable start is often more correct for a singing context.
	This is unique to rhotics surrounded by two vowels.
	Please use own discretion.
